Kganyago was addressing the media at the conclusion of their deliberations in Washington. 

The United States (US) stuck to its guns in calling out what it called unfair global trade practices that impede US and global growth but the IMFC, agreed that increasing trade was critical to broad-based economic growth.

The question of land expropriation without compensation was also put to the International Monetary Fund Chief, Christine Lagarde. 

